%%{init: {'theme':'neutral', 'themeVariables': {'fontSize':'15px'}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Caller as Hall button / cabin panel
    participant ES as ElevatorSystem
    participant DS as DispatchStrategy
    participant E as Elevator (chosen car)
    participant Q as upStops / downStops
    participant W as control-loop thread

    Caller->>ES: requestElevator(floor, dir, onArrive)
    activate ES
    ES->>ES: dispatchLock.lock()
    ES->>DS: choose(elevators, floor, dir)
    DS-->>ES: bestCar
    ES->>E: submit(new VisitFloorCommand(floor, onArrive))
    activate E
    E->>Q: offer(command)  [up if floor>current, down if floor<current]
    E->>E: workAvailable.signalAll()
    deactivate E
    ES->>ES: dispatchLock.unlock()
    ES-->>Caller: carId
    deactivate ES

    Note over E,W: W is a separate thread, running Elevator.run() the whole time

    W->>E: state.next(elevator)  (IdleState, parked)
    E-->>W: wakes — awaitWork() returns a direction
    loop until arrived
        W->>E: state.next(elevator)  (MovingState)
        E->>Q: peek()  (nearest stop this direction)
        E->>E: stepToward(target)  — one floor, one tick
    end
    W->>E: state.next(elevator)  (DoorsOpenState)
    E->>Q: poll() + execute(elevator)  for every command at this floor
    E->>Caller: onArrive.run()
    E->>E: dwellAtDoors(), then decide next direction
